5000|$|Swiatkowska {{was born}} in Tychy, Poland. At {{fourteen}} she entered the Lyceum of Art in Bielsko-Biala, and at sixteen she immigrated to New York City, where she attended Cooper Union School of Art. [...] She is the illustrator of fifteen children's books, including A Not Scary Story About Big <b>Scary</b> <b>Things</b> by the poet C.K. Williams, and the author and illustrator of one, Queen on Wednesday. The book she illustrated, Infinity and Me, was a 2013 ALA Notable Children's Book, and was named a New York Times Best Illustrated Children's Book of 2012.|$|R
2500|$|Empire {{magazine}} {{named it}} the fifth best film of 2008. The French film journal Cahiers du Cinéma named {{the film as}} the third best of 2008. Bloody Disgusting ranked the film number twenty in their list of the [...] "Top 20 Horror Films of the Decade", with the article calling the film [...] "A brilliant conceit, to be sure, backed by a genius early marketing campaign that followed the less-is-more philosophy to tantalizing effect... much like Blair Witch nearly ten years earlier, Cloverfield helped prove, particularly in its first half hour, that what you don't see can be the <b>scariest</b> <b>thing</b> of all." ...|$|R
